FT  21 APR 94 / UK Company News: OEM falls Pounds 92,000 into the red
Including three months contribution from Dev-Tech, OEM, the property
developer and investment concern - formerly Office and Electronic Machines -
suffered pre-tax losses of Pounds 92,000 for the six months ended December
31, compared with profits of Pounds 94,000.
Turnover amounted to Pounds 1.25m, against Pounds 2.3m which included Pounds
721,000 for the discontinued stationery and furniture business. Losses per
share were 0.6p (1.5p earnings).
